      'Some work stress is normal; too much hurts your health and performance. The goal isn’t zero stress — it’s to keep it at a level you can handle and to recover when it spikes.',
      'Identify what’s actually stressing you. Is it volume of work, unclear expectations, conflict with someone, or lack of control? Naming it helps you choose a response. Sometimes the fix is boundary-setting (saying no, turning off notifications after hours); sometimes it’s a conversation with your manager about priorities or support.',
