      'A VPN does not make you anonymous. The VPN provider can see your traffic (unless they’re designed not to log it). It doesn’t stop tracking by websites, cookies, or apps. For strong privacy, you need good habits (strong passwords, avoiding sketchy sites) and possibly other tools too.',
      'Do you need one? If you’re on public Wi‑Fi a lot or want to change your apparent location, a reputable VPN can be worth it. For everyday home use on your own connection, it’s optional. Choose a provider with a clear no-log policy and independent audits if you care about trust.',
